ry, age 29). Eldest son of Simeon Hart of Burlington and Mary Warner of Middletown. Ordained Wolcott CT Congregational minister Dec 4, 1811; died of dysentery the same year as his eldest son.","mother_research_notes":"Harriet Morris Hart (b. April 6, 1786 East Haven CT; d. Feb 23, 1839, age 53). Daughter of Amos Morris and Betsey Woodward of East Haven. Lived to see her surviving son Edward Lucas educated and established as an educator."},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"H01623","children_ids":["H02966","H02967","H02968","H02969","H02970","H02971"],"date_year":1837,"date_month":4,"date_day":26,"marriage_number":1}],"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":["educator","deacon","yale_graduate","yale_connection"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909, entry 1623 (in connection with Nancy Champion Hooker)"},{"short":"Hart Genealogy 1875 (Andrews)","full":"Genealogical history of Deacon Stephen Hart and his descendants, 1632-1875","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Geneological_history_of_Deacon_Stephen_Hart_and_his_descendants%2C_1632._1875%2C_%28IA_geneologicalhist01andr%29.pdf"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"education":[{"institution":"Yale College","institution_id":"INST022","location":"New Haven, Connecticut","end_year":1836,"degree":"A.B.","notes":"Fitted for college under his uncle Simeon Hart's care and direction."}],"career":[{"role":"Classical school proprietor","organization":"New Haven CT (his own school)","notes":"Resolved to make teaching his profession; opened a classical school in New Haven CT after Yale graduation."},{"role":"Principal","organization":"Berlin Academy CT","notes":"Transferred from his New Haven classical school to charge of the Berlin Academy."},{"role":"Associate principal","organization":"Simeon Hart's boarding school for boys, Farmington CT","notes":"Permanently relocated to Farmington as associate principal with his uncle Simeon Hart in the notable Simeon Hart School. After Simeon's death, Edward established his own school in Farmington — many graduates entered college or went directly into mercantile careers."},{"role":"Director","organization":"Farmington Savings Bank","notes":"Director of the Farmington Savings Bank."},{"role":"Deacon","organization":"Farmington Congregational Church","start_year":1854,"notes":"Chosen deacon of the Farmington Church in 1854."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"Born posthumously after his father's dysentery death","body":"Rev. Lucas Hart died of dysentery on Oct 16, 1813. Edward Lucas was born on Dec 31, 1813 — eleven weeks later. His older brother Edward, age 1, had died of the same dysentery five days before their father.","number":1},{"header":"Ran his uncle Simeon Hart's Farmington school","body":"After teaching in New Haven and serving as principal of the Berlin Academy, Edward Lucas Hart was associate principal at the Simeon Hart School in Farmington — the notable boarding school for boys his uncle had founded. After Simeon's death, Edward established his own Farmington school, where 'many young men entered college or went directly into mercantile pursuits.'","number":2}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM009","plot_notes":"Grove Street Cemetery, New Haven CT (Findagrave)."},"bio":{"title":"Deacon","first_name":"Edward","middle_name":"Lucas","last_name":"Hart","married_names":[],"display_name":"Deacon Edward Lucas Hart"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"alumnus"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"edward-hart-1813"},"H02966":{"id":"H02966","former_ids":["HD3160"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{